(Photo: Rick Osentoski-USA TODAY Sports) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
If most people hadn't seen it, they wouldn't have believed it. Michigan led by two in a hard-fought game with Michigan State with just seconds remaining. On fourth down, they elected to punt from around midfield. The punter mishandled the snap and State picked it up and ran it 38 yards for the score to win with no time left, stunning the partisan Michigan crowd.
